surface at the point of attack.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,958
Brace for impact, men!

9
00:00:24,041 --> 00:00:27,083
[CREW C] We should be
arriving momentarily, sir.

10
00:00:27,166 --> 00:00:31,125
[KAI] Sun, my love, bride of
my heart, I'll see you soon.

11
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,416
[NARRATOR]
Beneath the gently rolling

12
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,500
waves of the Seto Inland Sea.

13
00:00:38,583 --> 00:00:42,208
Young Nagasumi's life is saved,
and forever changed.

14
00:00:42,291 --> 00:00:45,875
But as with any debt,
this one too must be repaid.

15
00:00:45,958 --> 00:00:47,750
So our story begins.

16
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:52,375
Please humor them with a smile,
for young love is never easy.

17
00:00:55,083 --> 00:01:00,041
♪

18
00:02:30,458 --> 00:02:33,291
[CLASS REP] Ready?
All right, girls. Here we go!

19
00:02:34,541 --> 00:02:36,250
[LUNAR] Sun, that one's yours.

20
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,208
[SUN]  'Kay!

21
00:02:38,666 --> 00:02:40,000
[LUNAR] Sun!

22
00:02:40,083 --> 00:02:42,041
You just hit a celebrity
in the face with a volleyball!

23
00:02:42,125 --> 00:02:44,583
[SUN] Sorry, I'm not
so good with sports.

24
00:02:44,666 --> 00:02:45,958
[Lunar laughs]

25
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,208
Obviously you're
still jealous

26
00:02:47,291 --> 00:02:48,583
of our huge popularity!

27
00:02:48,666 --> 00:02:50,750
You hit us on purpose to
get back at us, didn't you?

28
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:53,458
Oh, the life of a star can
certainly be trying at times.

29
00:02:53,541 --> 00:02:54,333
[MAWARI] Serve!

30
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:55,541
[CLASS REP] Here goes!

31
00:02:57,083 --> 00:02:58,083
[LUNAR] You did it again!

32
00:02:58,166 --> 00:02:59,458
[SUN] Sorry, Lunar!

33
00:02:59,541 --> 00:03:00,375
[NAGASUMI]
I never can tell if they're

34
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:01,750
getting along or not.

35
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:03,666
Stop it! Quit running
around like that.

36
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,916
You two can't compete
without causing trouble.

37
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,750
Oh no. Here come
all the useless boys!

38
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:09,708
These guys would
make a real nice snack?

39
00:03:09,791 --> 00:03:12,000
Mr. Fujishiro,
please don't joke.

40
00:03:12,625 --> 00:03:14,500
What the--
What was that?

41
00:03:14,916 --> 00:03:16,833
Hey Nagasumi, there are
strange sounds

42
00:03:16,916 --> 00:03:17,833
coming from the ground here.

43
00:03:17,916 --> 00:03:19,500
What kind of sounds?

44
00:03:19,583 --> 00:03:21,625
Hey, what the hell?

45
00:03:21,708 --> 00:03:23,166
What's going on?

46
00:03:23,916 --> 00:03:27,166
[students cry out]

47
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:31,916
Whoa! A submarine came up
from below the gym floor?

48
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,666
[KAI] Sun Seto!

49
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:37,458
I've come for ya, Sun.
I'm here to pick ya up, my love.

50
00:03:40,541 --> 00:03:42,375
[NAGASUMI] Hey! Who
the hell do you think you are?

51
00:03:42,458 --> 00:03:43,583
[KAI] Glad ya asked me that.

52
00:03:43,666 --> 00:03:45,333
I am the first son
of the Mikawas,

53
00:03:45,416 --> 00:03:47,666
the famous military
family from Mikawa Bay,

54
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:48,750
an area that has yielded

55
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:50,583
three of history's
greatest generals.

56
00:03:50,666 --> 00:03:52,875
That's who the
hell I think I am.

57
00:03:52,958 --> 00:03:54,958
Kai Mikawa.

58
00:03:55,458 --> 00:03:56,958
What's with the overblown
hood ornament?

59
00:03:57,041 --> 00:03:59,250
Did he get that at an undersea
flea market or something?

60
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:01,166
[KAI]
You're Nagasumi Mischishio!

61
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:03,166
The one who kidnapped
my pretty Sun!

62
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:05,125
[NAGASUMI] I didn't kidnap her,
you pompous sea slug!

63
00:04:05,208 --> 00:04:06,916
And what are you to her anyway?

64
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,041
You're wastin' your breath!

65
00:04:08,125 --> 00:04:10,041
Prepare to be
filleted kidnapper!

66
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:11,291
Gonna die now.

67
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:12,375
[CLASS REP] Here goes!

68
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:15,500
[BOTH] Oh yea!

69
00:04:15,583 --> 00:04:17,750
[KAI] Usin' a cannonball?
That's low.

70
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:20,125
[NAGASUMI] But using a sword
on an unarmed man isn't low?

71
00:04:20,208 --> 00:04:21,583
[MAWARI] Hey. New kid!

72
00:04:21,666 --> 00:04:22,875
Kai Mikawa,
or whatever the hell

73
00:04:22,958 --> 00:04:24,083
you said your name was.

74
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:25,625
First you bust through
the floor in a sub,

75
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:27,625
and then you break the
weapons control law?

76
00:04:27,708 --> 00:04:28,666
How about I give you some

77
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:30,708
lessons in the rules
of this society.

78
00:04:30,791 --> 00:04:32,416
What if your actions had
gotten somebody hurt?

79
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:34,000
Bet ya didn't think
about that, did ya?

80
00:04:34,083 --> 00:04:35,583
[VOICES] That already happened!

81
00:04:35,666 --> 00:04:38,666
I see, ya gotta good
point there, I must admit.

82
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:41,208
I apologize.
That was rude of me.

83
00:04:41,291 --> 00:04:42,875
I'll see to it that my
conglomerate pays

84
00:04:42,958 --> 00:04:44,583
for any damage I've
done to the school.

85
00:04:44,666 --> 00:04:47,791
And I'll compensate
everybody here.

86
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:50,083
[SARU] (oh-oh-ah-ah)
Money, money, money! It's money!

87
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:51,458
[NAGASUMI]
It's a miracle. He's healed!

88
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:52,583
[MAWARI THINKS]
His conglomerate?

89
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:53,791
[MAWARI] That sounds
familiar somehow.

90
00:04:53,875 --> 00:04:55,416
You must be talking
about the Mikawa Group,

91
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,791
part of the Chukyo
Industrial Zone

92
00:04:56,875 --> 00:04:58,291
and a name known
throughout the world.

93
00:04:58,375 --> 00:05:00,583
So you're a member of the
richest family in the country?

94
00:05:00,666 --> 00:05:01,916
Sorry for the
grand entrance

95
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,958
and tearing up the floor
with my submarine here.

96
00:05:04,041 --> 00:05:06,166
I actually had a big
network of canals made

97
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:08,958
for submarine use specially
built under the city.

98
00:05:09,041 --> 00:05:12,000
[KAI] See, it's how I travel.
I go everywhere by submarine.

99
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:13,416
He built a canal network?

100
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:14,791
[GIRL A] Oh my gosh!
He's totally rich!

101
00:05:14,875 --> 00:05:16,208
[GIRL B] The Mikawa
conglomerate?

102
00:05:16,291 --> 00:05:17,583
That's super cool!

103
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:19,875
Bein' nice ta the ladies
is an important family rule.

104
00:05:19,958 --> 00:05:23,375
I do hope you'll accept
my sincere apology, Mawari.

105
00:05:23,458 --> 00:05:24,708
You're under
arrest for weapons

106
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:27,333
violations, property
damage, and for bribery.

107
00:05:27,916 --> 00:05:29,041
[GIRL A ] Don't do it, Mawari!

108
00:05:29,125 --> 00:05:31,083
[GIRL B] Oh, that
poor little rich boy!

109
00:05:31,166 --> 00:05:32,666
Loaded, influential,
and a ladies' man.

110
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:34,833
He's definitely the type of guy
who normally pisses me off.

111
00:05:34,916 --> 00:05:36,625
But somehow I still want
to be friends with him.

112
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:38,416
Hey, whose side
are you on, anyway?

113
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:39,708
[KAI] Please listen to me!

114
00:05:39,791 --> 00:05:41,000
What I've done
has scared the

115
00:05:41,083 --> 00:05:43,166
nice ladies here and
for that I'm truly sorry,

116
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,000
but I did it all for her sake.

117
00:05:45,083 --> 00:05:47,583
It was for Sun Seto, my bride.

118
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:49,250
Huh?
His bride?

119
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:51,875
And, Nagasumi, I hear that
ya know that Sun's a mermaid.

120
00:05:51,958 --> 00:05:53,500
You're a pretty low
down rat usin'

121
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:56,166
the threat of exposure ta bring
her ta Saitama against her will!

122
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,416
That's quite a
dirty trick ta pull.

123
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:58,875
I'd never do
anything like that.

124
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:01,958
But if you know about Sun.
You must be a mermaid, too.

125
00:06:02,041 --> 00:06:04,083
[KAI] That's right. I'm a
member of the proud orca race.

126
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:05,416
[NAGASUMI] Great,
this one's an orca?

127
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,083
[SARU] Sun's is
this guy's bride?

128
00:06:07,166 --> 00:06:08,166
[MAWARI] 
"Brought against her will?" 

129
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:09,291
Oh don't worry
about that stuff.

130
00:06:09,375 --> 00:06:10,500
This guy's just delusional.

131
00:06:10,583 --> 00:06:11,541
Now give me back my

132
00:06:11,625 --> 00:06:13,458
rightful bride,
Nagasumi Michishio.

133
00:06:13,541 --> 00:06:14,625
You shut up,
submarine boy.

134
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:15,666
Like hell she's your bride.

135
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,083
You don't even
have the first clue

136
00:06:17,166 --> 00:06:18,791
how rough it is to have
Sun as your bride, you idiot!

137
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:21,083
Is it that hard
on you, Nagasumi?

138
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:22,541
No, Sun, that
just slipped out.

139
00:06:22,625 --> 00:06:24,375
"Heat of the moment"
and all that.

140
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:27,333
[KAI] I'll have ya know,

141
00:06:27,416 --> 00:06:28,875
Sun is a childhood
friend of mine.

142
00:06:28,958 --> 00:06:31,958
She's the only one who truly
understands my innermost soul.

143
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:33,708
Yes, it was but a
mere four years ago,

144
00:06:33,791 --> 00:06:35,791
at the age of ten,
I was very shy

145
00:06:35,875 --> 00:06:37,583
and terrified of the world.

146
00:06:37,666 --> 00:06:40,708
[KAI] A yakuza had come to
visit my grandpa on business.

147
00:06:40,791 --> 00:06:43,083
And he'd brought his
little daughter with him.

148
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:44,583
My girl Sun.

149
00:06:44,666 --> 00:06:46,625
[KAI] There she was. Sun Seto.

150
00:06:48,208 --> 00:06:49,750
[SUN (YOUNG)]
Hey! You're Kai, right?

151
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:52,208
The boy who lives here?
Whatcha doin'?

152
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:54,083
If yer not busy, do ya
wanna talk to me?

153
00:06:54,166 --> 00:06:55,666
[KAI (YOUNG)] No. Just go away.

154
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:56,666
[SUN (YOUNG)]
Ya won't talk to me?

155
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:57,916
But why not?

156
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,750
Hey, ya don't hafta
cry about it er anything.

157
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:00,916
[SUN (YOUNG)]
Maybe it's my fault.

158
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,875
I must not be good
at talkin' ta people.

159
00:07:02,958 --> 00:07:04,166
I mean, I have
this friend Lunar,

160
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:05,791
and I always seem
ta be sayin' stuff

161
00:07:05,875 --> 00:07:08,375
that sets her off,
but I never know why.

162
00:07:09,416 --> 00:07:10,666
I think you're
actually pretty lucky

163
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:12,333
that you've got friends
you can fight with.

164
00:07:12,416 --> 00:07:14,291
How can fighting
make me lucky?

165
00:07:14,375 --> 00:07:15,666
[KAI (YOUNG)] Everyone
who talks ta me only cares

166
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:17,750
about money and power,
so they jus' suck up ta me.

167
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:19,166
Grown-ups and kids fall all over

168
00:07:19,250 --> 00:07:21,166
themselves tryin' ta
get on my good side.

169
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:22,708
[SUN (YOUNG)] Really?
I don't care much about

170
00:07:22,791 --> 00:07:25,583
money or power, and I
don't know how to suck up.

171
00:07:25,666 --> 00:07:27,333
Sometimes people
call me an airhead though.

172
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:29,416
I'm sick of it.

173
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,541
Well I think you're probably
fine just the way you are.

174
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:33,041
[SUN (YOUNG)] That was
a really nice thing ta say!

175
00:07:33,125 --> 00:07:34,708
Oh, well, bein' nice
to the ladies at all

176
00:07:34,791 --> 00:07:37,375
times is kinda this important
rule that my family has.

177
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:38,625
[SUN (YOUNG)] You're
going ta be nice ta me?

178
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,958
Okay, then why don't
you and I play house?

179
00:07:41,041 --> 00:07:41,916
You can be the family boss,

180
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,333
Kai, and I'll be
the footsoldier.

181
00:07:43,416 --> 00:07:45,416
Um, Sun, that's
an odd kind of family.

182
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,666
This'll be the front
door right here, okay?

183
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:49,541
Okay, sure.
That's the front door.

184
00:07:49,625 --> 00:07:50,666
[Sun mimics a door creaking]

185
00:07:50,750 --> 00:07:52,208
Boss we've got
a really big problem!

186
00:07:52,291 --> 00:07:55,083
Someone from a rival
gang's shot Masa.

187
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:57,416
And Fujishiro's taken matters
into his own hands and gone to

188
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:58,916
stage a raid on the Naruto gang!

189
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,291
Should we send Nakajima
to bring him back

190
00:08:00,375 --> 00:08:02,375
or should we storm in
with reinforcements?

191
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:03,750
I guess the way
I play house is

192
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:05,708
kinda different from the way
other people do it, huh?

193
00:08:05,791 --> 00:08:08,083
[KAI (YOUNG)] Yeah, why don't
we try a more normal version?

194
00:08:08,166 --> 00:08:09,791
Yeah, then I'll
be the mom 'kay?

195
00:08:09,875 --> 00:08:12,250
And I'll be the
submarine, okay?

196
00:08:12,666 --> 00:08:14,583
Yeah, submarines
are really nice.

197
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:15,916
All dark, cozy.

198
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,916
[SUN (YOUNG)] Uh, yeah,
submarines are real cool.

199
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,625
I-I can give it a try, I guess.

200
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:21,625
[KAI (YOUNG)]
Oh look, it's home port!

201
00:08:21,708 --> 00:08:24,625
Aoogah!
Woosh! I'm back!

202
00:08:24,708 --> 00:08:26,041
[SUN (YOUNG)]
Welcome home, dear.

203
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:28,791
Would you like to refuel?
Do you need some repairs?

204
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:31,500
Those were the most enjoyable
hours of my whole life.

205
00:08:31,583 --> 00:08:32,500
[NAGASUMI] That's
what it means to have

206
00:08:32,583 --> 00:08:33,875
someone understand your soul?

207
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:35,416
[KAI] If ya don't
open up to folks,

208
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,791
they'll never show you
who they really are either.

209
00:08:37,875 --> 00:08:40,416
That's the lesson that I
learned from Sun that day.

210
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:43,166
So he's had it bad
for Sun. Poor boy.

211
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:44,541
If that's the case,
maybe we need to

212
00:08:44,625 --> 00:08:46,708
teach him what a
truly cute girl is like.

213
00:08:46,791 --> 00:08:49,458
[LUNAR] You're the eldest
son of the Mikawa family?

214
00:08:50,041 --> 00:08:52,666
I'm so very honored
to meet you, sir!

215
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:54,000
And you're a pop singer.

216
00:08:54,083 --> 00:08:55,625
You are famous,
and I will admit that

217
00:08:55,708 --> 00:08:58,166
you're certainly a
beautiful young lady,

218
00:08:58,250 --> 00:09:00,833
but I'm afraid that you're
nothing compared to Sun.

219
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:02,791
[LUNAR] Wh-What?

220
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,791
[LUNAR] No, this can't be!
How could a celebrity like us

221
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:08,916
lose to someone
as ordinary as Sun?

222
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,416
[LUNAR] We can't accept this!
It's time for a rematch, Sun.

223
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:12,541
We'll show you who's cuter!

224
00:09:12,625 --> 00:09:14,291
We can out cute you
any day of the week!

225
00:09:14,375 --> 00:09:16,250
[MAWARI] Stop it, you two.
No fighting!

226
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:17,583
[SHARK] I can snack now?

227
00:09:17,666 --> 00:09:19,458
[MAWARI] I told you not
to joke around like that!

228
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:21,541
[KAI] Nagasumi Michishio,
of course I can

229
00:09:21,625 --> 00:09:23,375
understand why
you're drawn to Sun.

230
00:09:23,458 --> 00:09:24,750
[NAGASUMI] Oh yeah?

231
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,166
[KAI] She's not only pretty,
but charming and kind.

232
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:27,833
She'll be patient and sweet even

233
00:09:27,916 --> 00:09:29,750
with a real shy kid
like I used ta be.

234
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:31,500
A girl like Sun is
more precious than

235
00:09:31,583 --> 00:09:33,791
the biggest, most beautiful
pearl in the world.

236
00:09:33,875 --> 00:09:36,125
[KAI] She's a true miracle
from underneath the sea.

