00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:38,083
[KAI] Do ya really think
she'll be happier with you?

238
00:09:38,166 --> 00:09:39,791
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Money, power, and looks?

239
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:41,208
He totally beats me.

240
00:09:41,291 --> 00:09:43,916
I'm too young to be faced
with such a harsh reality.

241
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,833
[KAI] If you really do
want what's best for Sun,

242
00:09:45,916 --> 00:09:48,333
don't you think
you should back off?

243
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:51,625
Is it money ya want?
Huh? How much?

244
00:09:51,708 --> 00:09:52,791
Name your price.

245
00:09:52,875 --> 00:09:54,333
How much cash will
it take for a weakling

246
00:09:54,416 --> 00:09:57,333
like you to be willing
to give up Sun to me?

247
00:09:57,416 --> 00:09:59,791
[NAGASUMI] You're serious!
That just made up my mind!

248
00:09:59,875 --> 00:10:01,541
No way am I ever handing Sun

249
00:10:01,625 --> 00:10:03,500
over to an obnoxious
jerk like you!

250
00:10:03,583 --> 00:10:05,041
[KAI] Then I'm afraid
I have no choice but

251
00:10:05,125 --> 00:10:07,625
ta cut ya into pieces,
Nagasumi Michishio!

252
00:10:07,708 --> 00:10:09,958
Kai Mikawa!

253
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:11,625
[KAI] Pitiful human!

254
00:10:11,708 --> 00:10:14,333
You'll never beat
a merman like me!

255
00:10:16,083 --> 00:10:18,916
Huh? The sky?

256
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,000
[KAI] The outdoors!

257
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:22,166
It's bright and
wide open with no walls!

258
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:24,958
[KAI] Help me! scary!

259
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,416
[KAI] It happened
when I was six.

260
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,833
I went along with my grandpa
on a job that he had,

261
00:10:28,916 --> 00:10:30,833
and I got lost in
the Sahara Desert!

262
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:33,500
I've been scared of bright,
wide-open places ever since.

263
00:10:33,583 --> 00:10:34,958
That's why I hid from the world.

264
00:10:35,041 --> 00:10:37,625
I like dark, confined places
with walls to protect me!

265
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:39,666
Well, I guess that explains
the submarines, then.

266
00:10:40,041 --> 00:10:42,291
[KAI] Please somebody help me!
I'll pay whatever you want.

267
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:43,958
Anything!
Just help me!

268
00:10:44,041 --> 00:10:45,833
[SUN] Now hold
on a minute.

269
00:10:45,916 --> 00:10:47,125
[NAGASUMI] Yes, Sun?

270
00:10:47,208 --> 00:10:49,416
The Kai I knew four
years ago hated people

271
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:50,708
who swarmed around
money and power

272
00:10:50,791 --> 00:10:52,250
just to make themselves
seem important.

273
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:54,041
But now here
ya are, throwin' money

274
00:10:54,125 --> 00:10:56,333
at every problem ya come across.

275
00:10:56,416 --> 00:10:57,583
[SUN] You're the one
who's become obsessed

276
00:10:57,666 --> 00:10:59,083
with money and power now, Kai.

277
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:01,000
How could you?

278
00:11:02,291 --> 00:11:03,916
[SUN] If ya need help,
ya can call on me

279
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,708
anytime, but without the money.

280
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:09,416
Sun, my love.

281
00:11:15,291 --> 00:11:17,708
[KAI] Thank you, Sun.
You've taught me yet

282
00:11:17,791 --> 00:11:19,416
another valuable lesson today.

283
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,875
I'll return once I've changed.

284
00:11:21,958 --> 00:11:24,041
[KAI] As for you,
Nagasumi Michishio.

285
00:11:24,125 --> 00:11:26,833
We'll table our fight
until next we meet.

286
00:11:26,916 --> 00:11:29,000
[NAGASUMI] And so,
with mixed emotions,

287
00:11:29,083 --> 00:11:32,625
we watched Kai Mikawa
disappear beneath the gym floor.

288
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,208
Okay class, we've got yet

289
00:11:35,291 --> 00:11:37,125
another new
transfer student today.

290
00:11:37,208 --> 00:11:39,000
[GOZABURO]
His name is Kai Mikawa.

291
00:11:39,083 --> 00:11:41,375
I decided I'd do my
learnin' at this school.

292
00:11:41,458 --> 00:11:43,375
I'm lookin' forward
to workin' with all of ya'.

293
00:11:43,458 --> 00:11:45,208
[NAGASUMI]
Hey, you didn't leave!

294
00:11:47,208 --> 00:11:48,375
[CLASS REP]
All right, we need to start

295
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:50,291
dividing up duties
for next week's field day.

296
00:11:50,375 --> 00:11:51,625
Everyone should decide what

297
00:11:51,708 --> 00:11:53,750
events they
want to participate--

298
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,666
[GIRL 2] I want to do the
three-legged race with you.

299
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:58,333
[CLASS REP] Everyone!
Please listen for a second!

300
00:11:58,416 --> 00:11:59,666
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
This guy actually had the nerve

301
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:01,708
to say he'd make
Sun happier than me.

302
00:12:01,791 --> 00:12:04,166
He's behaving himself
now, but we'll see.

303
00:12:04,250 --> 00:12:06,375
You'll be split into the
red team and the white team.

304
00:12:06,458 --> 00:12:07,416
Here we go!

305
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:08,791
A challenge, Nagasumi!

306
00:12:08,875 --> 00:12:10,291
What? Why me?

307
00:12:10,375 --> 00:12:12,208
[KAI] I came to this school to
settle the score with ya.

308
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:14,166
This here is the
perfect opportunity.

309
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:17,000
I'll battle ya in the Field Day
events next week!

310
00:12:17,083 --> 00:12:17,916
[NAGASUMI] Huh?

311
00:12:18,541 --> 00:12:20,208
Ya think ya can beat me?

312
00:12:20,291 --> 00:12:21,375
You're on.

313
00:12:21,458 --> 00:12:23,208
I'll pound you into
the ground, Mikawa.

314
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:26,541
[CLASS REP] Repeat after me:
I hereby swear to follow a

315
00:12:26,625 --> 00:12:28,625
spirit of sportsmanship and
engage only in fair--

316
00:12:28,708 --> 00:12:30,833
[SARU] Et cetera, the end.

317
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:34,000
The fight's on now. Prepare
to lose to me, Nagasumi!

318
00:12:34,083 --> 00:12:35,625
Hah! We'll see
about that, Mikawa!

319
00:12:35,708 --> 00:12:36,833
[CLASS REP] The first
event of the morning is

320
00:12:36,916 --> 00:12:38,208
the girls' hundred meter race.

321
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:39,750
Girls are you ready?

322
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:43,666
[CLASS REP] Why do have to
wear such a ridiculous outfit?

323
00:12:45,083 --> 00:12:45,791
You can do it, Sun. Go!

324
00:12:45,875 --> 00:12:47,708
[GOZABURO] Yeah, go!

325
00:12:47,791 --> 00:12:49,166
[GOZABURO] You can
win this thing Sun!

326
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:51,458
Anyone who dares
to run in front of you--

327
00:12:51,541 --> 00:12:52,875
[MASA] Boss, please calm down.

328
00:12:52,958 --> 00:12:54,541
Remember, you can't act
like this during school hours.

329
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:56,500
Dad, stop it.
Please sit down.

330
00:12:56,583 --> 00:12:58,875
A homeroom teacher shouldn't
show such blatant favoritism.

331
00:12:58,958 --> 00:13:00,958
Start acting
like a proper teacher!

332
00:13:01,041 --> 00:13:03,166
We're restarting. Go.

333
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:05,250
[SUN] Whew!

334
00:13:06,166 --> 00:13:07,375
[CLASS REP]
And next up we have the

335
00:13:07,458 --> 00:13:09,375
boys' two hundred meter race.

336
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:13,458
All right, now it's my turn.

337
00:13:13,541 --> 00:13:14,541
Mikawa's going
to be running the

338
00:13:14,625 --> 00:13:15,916
two hundred meter
for the white team.

339
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,958
And yet I don't see the
obnoxious jerk anywhere.

340
00:13:18,041 --> 00:13:20,041
Maybe he's forfeiting it, huh?

341
00:13:20,125 --> 00:13:22,375
[KAI] Sorry ta keep
ya waitin' Nagasumi.

342
00:13:22,458 --> 00:13:24,875
Wh-What the...

343
00:13:24,958 --> 00:13:26,208
[KAI] I found a solution.

344
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:28,750
By hermetically sealing
myself in this spacesuit,

345
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:31,708
I can conquer my fear of bright,
wide open, outside spaces.

346
00:13:31,791 --> 00:13:35,000
It's one small step for mankind,
but one giant leap for me.

347
00:13:35,083 --> 00:13:36,458
[SARU] Mikawa would
go this far for a fight?

348
00:13:36,541 --> 00:13:38,041
He must be really serious then.

349
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:40,250
Too bad he's not
in outer space, though.

350
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:42,000
[KAI] Hey, I'm gonna run in this
lane instead of you. Move.

351
00:13:42,083 --> 00:13:42,666
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
I didn't expect him to

352
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:44,041
go this far for Sun.

353
00:13:44,125 --> 00:13:45,208
[SHARK] Runners on your mark?

354
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:46,291
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
I can't lose this fight.

355
00:13:46,375 --> 00:13:47,833
[SHARK] Get set?

356
00:13:47,916 --> 00:13:49,291
[NAGASUMI THINKS] I'm gonna
beat this guy if it kills me.

357
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:55,541
[KAI] Hey! Wait!
Wait for me!

358
00:13:56,041 --> 00:13:57,458
Wow, Good job, Nagasumi.

359
00:13:57,541 --> 00:13:59,458
Oh, hey, it was
nothing, Sun.

360
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,000
[Kai breathing heavy]

361
00:14:03,083 --> 00:14:04,666
You gonna be okay?

362
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:06,208
I don't think the
spacesuit's working.

363
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:08,750
[KAI] I just didn't warm
up enough before I ran.

364
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:10,375
I'm sure. What was
the bet we made again?

365
00:14:10,458 --> 00:14:12,625
The loser can't go
after Sun anymore?

366
00:14:12,708 --> 00:14:14,875
[KAI] No, that wasn't it,
it was the losin' team!

367
00:14:14,958 --> 00:14:17,250
The one on the losin'
team has to stand down.

368
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:18,708
You dirty cheater.

369
00:14:18,791 --> 00:14:21,250
[LUNAR] Okay everybody,
next is the scavenger hunt race.

370
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:22,250
Are you ready?

371
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,750
[LUNA DUDES] Lunar! Lunar!

372
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:25,916
[CLASS REP] I'm just
not cut out for this.

373
00:14:28,208 --> 00:14:29,125
[NAGASUMI] Cute girl?

374
00:14:29,208 --> 00:14:30,083
[KAI] Cute guy?

375
00:14:30,166 --> 00:14:31,125
There can only
be one cute

376
00:14:31,208 --> 00:14:33,333
girl for me, and that's Sun!

377
00:14:33,416 --> 00:14:34,791
Nagasumi.

378
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:36,208
[Lunar laughs]

379
00:14:36,291 --> 00:14:38,375
We suppose we must do
this for the sake of victory.

380
00:14:38,458 --> 00:14:40,750
We'll allow you to take
us with you, Nagasumi!

381
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:41,750
[NAGASUMI] No!

382
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:42,958
Hey Lunar,
Nagasumi was

383
00:14:43,041 --> 00:14:44,333
going to pick me
as his cute girl.

384
00:14:44,416 --> 00:14:46,416
Silly Sun. We are
a professional celebrity.

385
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,208
Obviously, cute girl
can only mean us.

386
00:14:48,291 --> 00:14:49,750
Whatever anybody'll
do at this point!

387
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:51,375
Somebody come
be my cute girl, quick!

388
00:14:52,166 --> 00:14:53,708
[MAWARI] Oh all right,
I guess I'll be the cute girl.

389
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:56,125
But that doesn't mean I'm yours.

390
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:58,375
[CLASS REP] I'm the class rep,
so if anyone'll do, maybe I--

391
00:15:00,958 --> 00:15:02,791
[KAI] Huh?
What is this?

392
00:15:02,875 --> 00:15:04,875
I won the race,
and yet I'm cryin'

393
00:15:04,958 --> 00:15:06,083
a river of jealous tears.

394
00:15:06,166 --> 00:15:07,708
[MASA] Young master Mikawa.

395
00:15:07,791 --> 00:15:09,875
A man can only
shed his tears at

396
00:15:09,958 --> 00:15:12,208
the death of a parent
or when he's shamed.

397
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:15,875
[KAI] Maybe I was
right to choose

398
00:15:15,958 --> 00:15:17,208
him as my cute guy.

399
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,708
He seems to be very wise.

400
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:22,250
[ANNOUNCER] Next is
the cheering competition.

401
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:24,791
[VOICES] Be aggressive.
B-E aggressive!

402
00:15:24,875 --> 00:15:26,083
Why you little brat!

403
00:15:26,166 --> 00:15:27,541
What makes you think
you have the right to toss

404
00:15:27,625 --> 00:15:28,958
a baton in a little skirt and
steal all our attention?

405
00:15:29,041 --> 00:15:30,916
[SUN] Lunar, let me go.
I can't dance this way, ya see.

406
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,458
How're we gonna win
the cheering competition?

407
00:15:32,541 --> 00:15:33,708
--[LUNAR DUDES] Hail Lunar!
--[SUN DUDES] Sun's our light!

408
00:15:33,791 --> 00:15:35,125
[ANNOUNCER] Next will
be team white's entry

409
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:36,708
in the cheering competition.

410
00:15:37,958 --> 00:15:40,833
[MAWARI] Yea! Yea! Woo-hoo!

411
00:15:47,041 --> 00:15:48,125
[CLASS REP]
What's with these jerks.

412
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:49,833
Yeah, I know that
maybe I don't stand out

413
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:51,416
in a crowd even though
I'm the class rep.

414
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:52,708
But still, you'd think at least
one of them would know my name.

415
00:15:52,791 --> 00:15:54,250
[SARU] You've got some
pent up aggression, huh?

416
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:55,750
[ANNOUNCER] This
concludes our morning events.

417
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:57,750
It's now time for lunch break.

418
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:58,791
[NAGASUMI] Wow!

419
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:00,250
Did you really
make all this, Sun?

420
00:16:00,333 --> 00:16:02,541
[SUN] Uh-huh.
I worked really hard on it.

421
00:16:02,625 --> 00:16:03,625
[Lunar laughs mockingly]

422
00:16:03,708 --> 00:16:05,208
[LUNAR] Try this too.

423
00:16:05,291 --> 00:16:07,375
This is the lunch that we made.
You may have a bite, servant.

424
00:16:07,458 --> 00:16:08,166
It's tasty.

425
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,541
[NAGASUMI] Whoa!

426
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:11,500
I don't think that lunch
should look like modern art.

427
00:16:11,583 --> 00:16:12,833
I taught Lunar
how to make a very

428
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:14,708
special lunch just
for you Nagasumi,

429
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:16,750
and I expect
you to eat all of it.

430
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,500
[NAGASUMI] Right!
Thanks for the food!

431
00:16:18,583 --> 00:16:19,958
[MOM] Oh, and, Masa...

432
00:16:20,041 --> 00:16:23,083
I um. I made this
lunch just for you.

433
00:16:24,541 --> 00:16:26,833
[MASA] It does looks delicious,
and I do appreciate it.

434
00:16:26,916 --> 00:16:28,375
But I must decline.

435
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:29,625
[MOM THINKS]
Oh, I know it's wrong,

436
00:16:29,708 --> 00:16:31,166
but the more he pushes
away what I'm offering,

437
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:32,833
the more I want him to take it.

438
00:16:33,708 --> 00:16:34,958
[DAD'S BOSS]
Where's that report?

439
00:16:35,041 --> 00:16:37,625
If you've got time to eat,
you've got time to work.

440
00:16:37,708 --> 00:16:39,041
Right away, sir, sorry.

441
00:16:39,125 --> 00:16:40,458
[BUTLER]
Here you are, master Kai.

442
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:42,208
Your lunch buffet is prepared.

443
00:16:42,958 --> 00:16:45,583
[KAI THINKS] I feel an emptiness
that no food can satisfy.

444
00:16:45,666 --> 00:16:48,125
None but the food
prepared by beautiful Sun.

445
00:16:48,208 --> 00:16:50,791
Nagasumi I could
kill you for that lunch.

446
00:16:51,416 --> 00:16:53,125
[KAI THINKS] Money can't
be everything to me.

447
00:16:53,208 --> 00:16:55,458
What I really need is
a friend or someone to--

448
00:16:57,166 --> 00:16:59,833
[KAI] Do you, need
somethin' to eat, kid?

449
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:03,125
[KAI THINKS] I guess there's
always someone worse off.

450
00:17:03,208 --> 00:17:05,416
[KAI] Eat!

451
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,875
[ANNOUNCER ] The first
event of the afternoon

452
00:17:06,958 --> 00:17:08,833
is the mock cavalry battle.

453
00:17:08,916 --> 00:17:10,541
Kai Mikawa!

454
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:12,291
[KAI] Nagasumi Michishio!

455
00:17:12,375 --> 00:17:13,833
[NAGASUMI] Hey,
what's with the spear?

456
00:17:13,916 --> 00:17:15,500
We're supposed to steal each
other's' headbands, that's all!

457
00:17:15,583 --> 00:17:17,166
[KAI] Shut up! Take this!

458
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:18,375
I'm dead!

459
00:17:19,916 --> 00:17:21,375
[KAI] You collapsed.
What kinda horse are you?

460
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:23,250
Hey, if you weren't
so heavy to carry--!

461
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:24,458
[KAI] Why you!

462
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,666
[Kai gasps]

463
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,208
[KAI] Too bright!
Too wide-open!

464
00:17:31,291 --> 00:17:32,541
No walls!
Too scary!

465
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:33,416
Oh, I'm gonna die!

466
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:34,458
[NAGASUMI] He's freaking out.

467
00:17:34,541 --> 00:17:36,083
Here, my lord.

468
00:17:36,166 --> 00:17:37,666
[SARU] I have prepared an
extra space helmet

469
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:39,500
in case something
like this happened.

470
00:17:39,583 --> 00:17:41,375
[KAI] Kid, ya have my thanks.

471
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,041
This helmet is warm.
Did you try it on?

472
00:17:44,125 --> 00:17:46,541
Or maybe you sat on it
an' rested yer legs for a spell?

473
00:17:46,625 --> 00:17:47,583
Of course not, my lord.

474
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:49,083
I merely stuffed
it under my shirt

475
00:17:49,166 --> 00:17:50,291
and warmed it with my body heat

476
00:17:50,375 --> 00:17:52,375
for you so it would
be comfortable.

477
00:17:54,125 --> 00:17:54,958
[KAI] What's your name?

478
00:17:55,041 --> 00:17:56,166
Please call
me Chimp, sir.

479
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:57,333
[KAI] Chimp.

480
00:17:57,416 --> 00:17:58,708
I grant you a special
place in my army.

481
00:17:58,791 --> 00:18:00,916
[NAGASUMI] Chimp has
been won over by Mikawa?

482
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,458
[KAI] Take a good
look at that, Chimp.

483
00:18:02,541 --> 00:18:04,708
Those points virtually guarantee
that the white team'll win.

484
00:18:04,791 --> 00:18:07,041
[SARU] A huge victory
for our forces, my lord.

485
00:18:07,125 --> 00:18:09,166
Oh no, it looks
like Sun's team is losing.

486
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:11,916
What? My precious
Sun? She can't lose!

487
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,291
[GOZABURO] Attention please
After much deliberation,

488
00:18:14,375 --> 00:18:16,041
it has been decided
that the final event,

489
00:18:16,125 --> 00:18:19,083
the baton relay,
will be worth 333 points.

490
00:18:19,166 --> 00:18:21,250
Anyone who has a problem
with that can attend detention.

491
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:23,250
That's completely insane!

492
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:24,875
[KAI] What was that
announcement about?

493
00:18:24,958 --> 00:18:25,916
[SARU] My lord.

494
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,083
I don't believe
that anyone in this

495
00:18:27,166 --> 00:18:28,791
school has the power
to stop Mister Seto.

496
00:18:28,875 --> 00:18:30,958
[KAI] Very well. Nagsumi!

497
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,500
[KAI] I trust even a sea slug
like you understands

498
00:18:33,583 --> 00:18:35,416
why this battle is so important?

499
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,791
[NAGASUMI] It's for Sun, right?

500
00:18:36,875 --> 00:18:37,958
That's right!

501
00:18:38,041 --> 00:18:39,750
For this relay, the stakes
will be immense.

502
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:41,041
We fight for Sun.

503
00:18:41,125 --> 00:18:42,125
What?

504
00:18:42,208 --> 00:18:43,375
[KAI] Whoever loses
this relay agrees

505
00:18:43,458 --> 00:18:45,208
to give up on Sun
like a gentleman.

506
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:46,541
What do ya say?

507
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:47,541
Let's do it.

508
00:18:47,625 --> 00:18:48,833
No one in this
world can possibly

509
00:18:48,916 --> 00:18:50,375
care for Sun more than I do.

510
00:18:50,458 --> 00:18:51,625
[SUN] Nagasumi.

511
00:18:53,125 --> 00:18:54,208
[SUN] Did the two of ya make
me the stakes in this race?

512
00:18:54,291 --> 00:18:56,166
Sun, I can explain.
Really, I can.

513
00:18:56,583 --> 00:18:57,958
[SUN] All right, Nagasumi.

514
00:18:58,041 --> 00:19:00,000
If my husband has
put his wife on the line

515
00:19:00,083 --> 00:19:01,666
in a man-to-man
fight for his honor,

516
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:02,750
then I understand.

517
00:19:02,833 --> 00:19:06,000
I am ready to accept my fate.

518
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:07,333
I also have
a path of honor

519
00:19:07,416 --> 00:19:09,041
that I must follow at all costs.

520
00:19:09,125 --> 00:19:11,875
I live by the mermaid code.

521
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:15,791
'Cause honor among
thieves is honor under the seas.

522
00:19:16,750 --> 00:19:18,000
Wow. Sun.

523
00:19:18,375 --> 00:19:21,541
Ya see, Nagasumi.
I'll always believe in ya.

524
00:19:22,666 --> 00:19:23,791
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
This battle is definitely

525
00:19:23,875 --> 00:19:25,791
one that I can't lose.

526
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:27,208
[LUNAR] Woo-hoo!

527
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:29,375
If we win this relay,
we win it all!

528
00:19:29,458 --> 00:19:31,916
If you lose I'll arrest you!

529
00:19:34,250 --> 00:19:35,875
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Hurry up, baton.

530
00:19:35,958 --> 00:19:38,166
I've got Sun
on the line here.

531
00:19:38,250 --> 00:19:40,125
I can't let that
Kai bastard have her.

532
00:19:40,208 --> 00:19:42,333
There's no way
I can lose this one!

533
00:19:45,541 --> 00:19:47,000
[KAI THINKS] So the red
team is in the lead.

534
00:19:47,083 --> 00:19:48,791
How pointless.

535
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:49,958
There's a big
difference in the

536
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:52,291
stamina between
humans and merfolk.

537
00:19:52,375 --> 00:19:54,625
[KAI] Take this for me, Chimp.

538
00:19:54,708 --> 00:19:55,708
Oh, wow.

539
00:19:55,791 --> 00:19:56,875
He was actually
running with something

540
00:19:56,958 --> 00:19:58,625
this heavy on his
back this whole time?

541
00:19:58,708 --> 00:19:59,625
[SARU] My lord!

542
00:19:59,708 --> 00:20:01,875
Hey, what?
What is this?

543
00:20:01,958 --> 00:20:03,958
It's all over.

544
00:20:04,041 --> 00:20:06,666
Sun's going to
be mine at last.

545
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:10,000
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Damn it!

546
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:12,375
Damn it. Damn it!

547
00:20:13,083 --> 00:20:15,000
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Catch up. Catch up!

548
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:21,000
[NAGASUMI] Catch up!

549
00:20:22,791 --> 00:20:25,625
[KAI] Beached! Beached!

550
00:20:25,708 --> 00:20:28,000
[NAGASUMI THINKS] Was that
an orca I just saw on the track?

551
00:20:28,083 --> 00:20:29,666
[LUNAR AND SUN]
Flip flop, flip flop, flip.

552
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:31,291
[NAGASUMI] On no, not them too!

553
00:20:31,375 --> 00:20:32,458
[SUN] Oh dear.

554
00:20:32,541 --> 00:20:33,833
[LUNAR] It seems to be raining.

555
00:20:33,916 --> 00:20:36,250
This is bad! What if
the other students see?

556
00:20:37,083 --> 00:20:38,083
It's really pouring down.

557
00:20:38,166 --> 00:20:39,333
I can hardly see!

558
00:20:39,416 --> 00:20:40,583
--Red team wins!
--Can't see a thing in all this.

559
00:20:40,666 --> 00:20:42,750
How's the red team doin'?
Are they winning?

560
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:43,750
[KAI] This isn't fair!

561
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:44,833
I can't afford
to lose like this!

562
00:20:44,916 --> 00:20:46,333
Dammit! Why is this
happening to me?

563
00:20:46,416 --> 00:20:49,083
[SARU] My lord! My lord!

564
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:51,625
[students screaming]

565
00:20:53,375 --> 00:20:54,958
[STUDENTS]
Not this again!

566
00:20:55,041 --> 00:20:56,666
My lord, where
have you gone to?

567
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:59,416
Your servant Chimp has come
to aid you in your quest.

568
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,208
[NAGASUMI] What are you doing?

569
00:21:01,291 --> 00:21:02,375
[SARU] All hands on deck!

570
00:21:02,458 --> 00:21:04,125
The enemy is
within firing range!

571
00:21:04,208 --> 00:21:09,291
Current distance: 150 meters.
Fire!

572
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:13,208
[NAGASUMI] You'll do
anything for money! Help!

573
00:21:13,291 --> 00:21:15,500
[SUN] Don't worry, Nagsumi!
I'll help you!

574
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:17,458
With the powerful
ancient mermaid lyrics

575
00:21:17,541 --> 00:21:19,291
of the song of sleep!

576
00:21:19,375 --> 00:21:23,500
[SUN] ♪ Rally ho. Rally ho
Rally, rally, rally ho. ♪

577
00:21:23,583 --> 00:21:24,666
♪ Rally ho, rally ho.
Rally, rally, rally ho. ♪

578
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,125
[NAGASUMI] Oh whoa,
this song is really.

579
00:21:26,708 --> 00:21:28,708
[buzzers powering down]

580
00:21:28,791 --> 00:21:33,791
♪ Rally ho, rally ho.
Rally, rally, rally ho. ♪

581
00:21:36,666 --> 00:21:38,500
[students cry out]

582
00:21:43,291 --> 00:21:46,041
[CLASS REP] I wonder caused
that explosion on the track.

583
00:21:46,125 --> 00:21:47,625
[MAWARI] Maybe a gas pipe burst.

584
00:21:47,708 --> 00:21:49,333
When the rain lets up,
I'll make a thorough

585
00:21:49,416 --> 00:21:51,500
investigation into the cause.

586
00:21:51,583 --> 00:21:52,708
And the worst
part is we all missed

587
00:21:52,791 --> 00:21:54,416
the chance to settle
the field day battle.

588
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:55,708
It was so close.

589
00:21:55,791 --> 00:21:58,750
[SUN] Ah! Oh look!
I think the rain's stopped.

590
00:21:59,333 --> 00:22:01,541
[KAI THINKS] This ain't over
yet, Nagasumi Michishio.

591
00:22:01,625 --> 00:22:04,125
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Yeah. Okay. Whatever.

592
00:22:05,125 --> 00:22:10,083
♪

593
00:23:34,833 --> 00:23:36,208
[NAGASUMI] Yet another
member of the seafolk

594
00:23:36,291 --> 00:23:37,958
has come to disturb
life in Saitama--

595
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:40,541
with an iron body, a machine
brain, and tons of money!

596
00:23:40,625 --> 00:23:43,541
This crisis is unprecedented in
the life of Nagasumi Michishio.

597
00:23:43,625 --> 00:23:45,375
This guy terrifies me
more than I can take!

598
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:46,458
What should I do?

599
00:23:46,541 --> 00:23:48,583
I don't think I can
deal with this!

